HEADWORD: Outstay
<hw>Out*stay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To stay beyond or
longer than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She concluded to <qex>outstay</qex> him.</q> <rj><qau>Mad. D'
